items.title: Tribe's streak halted at 22 with loss to Royals
items.summary: With a 4-3 victory on Friday night, the Royals halted the Indians' AL-record run of 22 consecutive wins.
items.content: With a 4-3 victory on Friday night, the Royals halted the Indians' AL-record run of 22 consecutive wins.

items.title: Wood, Dodgers blank Nats, cut magic No. to 6
items.summary: Los Angeles blanked the Nationals on Friday night, 7-0, led by one of left-hander Alex Wood's best performances of late. Justin Turner, Yasiel Puig and Corey Seager all hit homers off right-hander Edwin Jackson to take the air out of the 37,508 fans in Washington and increase the Dodgers' lead to six games over the Nationals for the best record in the NL.
